<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="surprised-adj">surprised <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /sə'praɪzd/    美 /sər'praɪzd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>吃惊的；感到惊讶的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was surprised and delighted to win. 
能够获胜让我既惊讶又高兴。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) surprised at:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The staff were surprised at the fact. 
工作人员对事实感到惊讶。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) surprised to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A week later, I was surprised to find I got an A.
一周后，我惊奇地发现自己得了个A。</p><footer>2008 北京</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) surprised + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He’s surprised that he got the scholarship.  
他很惊讶自己获得了奖学金。</p></div></div>